I've compiled the core components and features of the 4D-Taki (4dtakki) project from our previous sessions. You were building this as a 3D evolution of Tic-Tac-Toe, targeting a mobile Android release using Android Studio and Capacitor.
Project Overview: 4D-Taki

The game operates on a 4x4x4 grid (64 total cells), significantly expanding the complexity of traditional Tic-Tac-Toe.
Core Mechanics & Win Logic

    Grid Dimensions: A three-dimensional 4x4x4 playing field.

    Win Conditions: There are 76 possible winning lines (horizontal, vertical, depth, and various 3D diagonals).

    Visual Feedback: The UI includes a feature to highlight the last piece placed to help players track movement in the 3D space.

Key Features

    AI & Strategy: Includes an AI opponent and a feature for LLM-driven strategic hints to assist the player.

    User Systems: Integrated Firebase for handling user accounts and tracking statistics (Wins, Losses, Draws, and Quits).

    Aesthetics: The interface features a dynamic space/nebula background.

Development Environment

    OS: Developing on Kali Linux.

    Frameworks: Built using Capacitor to bridge web code into a native Android APK.

    Automation: You have automated shell scripts prepared for the build process within Android Studio.
